                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18250915-245-off1312 t18250915-245-crimeloc1315"></join>. On the 15th of September, the prisoner came into the shop; I saw him going out, while I was speaking to a gentleman in a gig; he pretended to match a bit of print in his hand; I took hold of him, and found under his coat, these two handkerchiefs, which had hung behind the door.</p>
               <p>(Property produced and sworn to.)</p>
               <p>Prisoner's Defence. I did not intend to take them at all, I had not got them in my hand; they were hanging on my shoulder as I came out.</p>
